  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 45 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1640 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
time required: 20m
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/italian-herb-chicken-creamy-polenta-671952d3c2f9d9459122b885
---

Pat @chicken cutlets{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the
@Italian seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @black pepper{1%tsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off
heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise) lengthwise; slice into
½-inch-thick half-moons.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add zucchini;
season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned,
~{5-7%minutes}.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%oz}. Swap in asparagus for
zucchini. Cook, stirring, until lightly browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a small #pot{}, combine @precooked polenta{1} and @water{1/3%cup}
over medium heat. Mash with a #potato masher{} until mostly smooth, ~{30-60%seconds}
(remaining lumps will be broken up when whisking).

Whisk in @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
and @butter{1%tbsp}; simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and season with
salt and pepper if desired.

> TIP: If polenta seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide polenta between #bowls{} and top with chicken and zucchini. Serve.